This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring June 17, 2012, as Father's Day. The proclamation highlights the important role that fathers play in the lives of their children and the well-being of the nation. It emphasizes the responsibility of fathers to do right by their children and the negative impact on communities when fathers are absent. The proclamation also acknowledges the efforts of men who have stepped up as fathers and encourages the promotion of responsible fatherhood. The President directs the display of the flag on all government buildings and calls upon citizens to observe Father's Day with appropriate programs and activities.